Cell["\<\
It\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a well known fact that half-wave layers have no effect \
on reflectance or transmittance of assemblies, at wavelengths at which they \
are truly half-wave. So we can have a window twice as thick:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7294395930148087`*^9, 3.7294395945810685`*^9}, {
   3.7294396264058104`*^9, 3.72943974926853*^9}, {3.72944018304515*^9, 
   3.7294402090771685`*^9}, {3.729440245657893*^9, 3.7294402646147146`*^9}, {
   3.729440427268528*^9, 3.7294404382608323`*^9}, {3.7294405218455114`*^9, 
   3.729440558974693*^9}, 3.729440662518721*^9, {3.729441276883872*^9, 
   3.7294412773636103`*^9}, {3.7294413122119493`*^9, 3.729441397123704*^9}, {
   3.7294475812118187`*^9, 3.7294475812584443`*^9}, {3.729448284761656*^9, 
   3.7294482867373734`*^9}, {3.7294483906336813`*^9, 
   3.7294484194332523`*^9}, {3.7294485644408703`*^9, 3.7294485699132605`*^9}, 
